Sprott Precious Metals
Expertise and track record of innovation

Sprott is a globally recognized leader in precious metals investing. Over the years, we’ve designed and developed innovative investment products for investors – from equity and bullion mutual funds, to exchange-traded bullion and equity solutions – that address very specific needs within their portfolios.


SEE PRODUCT OFFERING »






Sprott Precious Metals Team
Our seasoned portfolio managers are supported by in-house technical advisors who possess a wealth of mining industry experience. Pictured left to right: Senior Portfolio Manager, Jason Mayer; Senior Portfolio Manager, Paul Wong; Portfolio Manager, Maria Smirnova; Associate Portfolio Manager, Shree Kargutkar; Economic Geologist, Andrew Jackson and, Precious Metal Strategist, Trey Reik.





Investment Approach


Team-based approach
Focused portfolios of 30-40 names
Emphasis on technical expertise
Use of options, short selling, ETFs and cash to reduce downside volatility













Why invest in precious metals


Portfolio diversifier - Gold and silver have historically shown low correlation to traditional asset classes 
Historical store of value 


What our gold team is seeing


We are likely in the early stages of the current gold bull market, driven by a global push to a negative interest rate policy, currency volatility and a high level of cross-asset class correlation. 
Gold and silver equities are trading at attractive valuations – companies have reduced their operating costs, while equity valuations are still at historic lows relative to the price of gold
The average 24 month return of gold equities following the market bottom of the last 7 bear markets was 117%.

The recent rally has the hallmarks of a trend...
Current bear market has matched historical bear market precedents in both duration and magnitude and is bouncing off bottom of +35 year channel.

Chart represents S&P/TSX Global Gold Index in $USD, Source:Bloomberg, As at May 29, 2016






